  "text": "We now state an important concentration inequality for determinantal point processes as well as a bound for the α p,q mixing coefficient. The next two results can be found as Theorem 3.6 in [CITATION_1] and Corollary 4.2 in [CITATION_2] respectively. It can be shown that if for all p, q > 0, α p,q (s) → 0 as s → ∞, then Ψ is mixing. For example, see Section 3 in [CITATION_3] .",
